Author: jl777c#5810
Content: it seems it might be a stake grinding attack, as the fake stake attack was more a resource exhaustion that crashed nodes, not able to gain funds

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: oh, sorry, reading further there is a second attack called "spent stake" that allows to amplify the apparent stake. so it behaves similarily to stake grinding, but i guess is easier to conduct

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: it seems a pretty simple bug to fix, apparently they allow to use a valid, but already spent utxo to stake with. that seems quite an oversight if it is true, but a lot of the PoS systems use the coinbase for staking, which bypasses most of the usual validity checks. original peercoin didnt have this vuln, but over the years the code was copied over and over and i guess the check for utxo being unspent got removed

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: for komodo PoS64 chains, the staking tx is not in the coinbase and must be spendable, so the spent stake attack does not apply
